    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIt seems the gx command to open urls is broken on Windows. It is working in v0.12.2. I couldn't find any open issues regarding it. The attached gif shows behaviour in v0.12.2 and v0.13.0 +375... nightly\n\n<img width=\"1615\" height=\"1089\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e298a8e5-fd3a-4fec-9dac-f14e442c7c4c\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n-- move cursor on a url\n:norm gx \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPressing gx on a url should open the link in a web browser\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-375+g1e06e95662\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nPowerShell 7.6.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
