            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "caused by slash normalization. I fixed the c code, should've realized this path calls `uv.spawn` directly as well. :(\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/6a87ef75b3f141e175399e87c5518ec11102877d/runtime/lua/vim/_core/system.lua#L320-L326\n`exepath` returns `c:/windows/system32/cmd.exe`\n\n@rsinghgit, as a temp workaround, could you please try to change `cmd = cmd1` to `cmd = cmd1:gsub(\"/\", \"\\\\\")`, then start with `nvim --luamod-dev`\n",
