        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> [@ntdiary](https://github.com/ntdiary) ok no worries, per [#39382](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39382) `exepath()` is one of the functions that we planned to always return `\\` slashes (except when 'shellslash' is enabled), can we do that?\n\nSure, then if this error occurs when `shellslash` is enabled, should we provide a clearer msg to users?\nWhile debugging, my first instinct was to treat `cmd.exe` as a special case, or try passing args the same way as in C, but `luv` seems to handle them a bit differently. I'll take another look tomorrow—it's already 1am here. :D",
